One Line Interview Answer

"ArgoCD is a GitOps continuous delivery tool for Kubernetes that automatically syncs your cluster state with what is defined in your Git repository"

How ArgoCD Works

Git Repo                    Kubernetes Cluster
────────                    ──────────────────
Deployment.yaml      →      ArgoCD watches Git
Service.yaml         →      compares with cluster
Ingress.yaml         →      finds differences
        ↓                           ↓
developer pushes        ArgoCD detects change
new version             auto applies to cluster
        ↓                           ↓
Git updated ✅          cluster updated ✅

ArgoCD vs Jenkins

Jenkins                         ArgoCD
───────                         ──────
push based                      pull based
Jenkins pushes to cluster       ArgoCD pulls from Git
CI + CD together                CD only
runs on trigger                 always watching
no drift detection              detects drift ✅
pipeline script                 declarative YAML
general purpose                 kubernetes specific

What is Drift Detection

Drift = cluster state differs from Git

Example:
  Git says: replicas: 3
  Someone manually changes to replicas: 1
        ↓
  ArgoCD detects drift
        ↓
  Status: OutOfSync ⚠️
        ↓
  Auto sync → fixes back to 3 ✅
  Manual sync → you decide when to fix

-----------------------------------------

GitHub Actions CAN do the same — but there is a fundamental difference:

How GitHub Actions deploys:

Developer pushes code
        ↓
GitHub Actions triggers
        ↓
Runs kubectl apply    ← PUSHES to cluster
        ↓
Done — forgets about it ❌
No more watching ❌

--------------------------
How ArgoCD deploys:

Developer pushes code
        ↓
ArgoCD detects Git change
        ↓
Pulls and applies     ← PULLS from Git
        ↓
Keeps watching forever ✅
Compares Git vs Cluster continuously ✅

---------------
The BIG difference — drift detection:

Someone runs:
kubectl edit deployment my-app
changes replicas 3 → 1 manually

GitHub Actions:
  Has no idea ❌
  Never detects it ❌
  Cluster stays wrong ❌

ArgoCD:
  Detects immediately ✅
  Git says 3 replicas
  Cluster has 1 replica
  OutOfSync! ⚠️
  Auto reverts to 3 ✅


Push based vs Pull based:

+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------------+
|                   | GitHub Actions            | ArgoCD                       |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------------+
| Type              | Push based                | Pull based                   |
| Deploys by        | Running kubectl apply     | Pulling from Git             |
| After deploy      | Forgets ✗                 | Keeps watching ✓             |
| Drift detection   | ✗ No                      | ✓ Yes                        |
| Auto heal         | ✗ No                      | ✓ Yes                        |
| Rollback          | Re-run pipeline           | Git revert or UI click       |
| Cluster access    | Needs kubeconfig in GitHub| ArgoCD inside cluster        |
| Security          | kubeconfig exposed ⚠      | No external access needed ✓  |
+-------------------+---------------------------+------------------------------+


Security difference:

GitHub Actions:
  Needs AWS credentials ⚠️
  Needs kubeconfig ⚠️
  Stored in GitHub secrets
  External system accessing cluster ⚠️

ArgoCD:
  Lives INSIDE cluster ✅
  Pulls from Git — no inbound access
  No credentials outside cluster ✅
  More secure ✅


Real difference in one line:

GitHub Actions = deploys ONCE and stops watching ❌

ArgoCD = deploys AND watches forever ✅
         Git is ALWAYS source of truth

